The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's plans to improve and streamline environmental reviews for major infrastructure projects. The administration aims to protect the environment while building new roads, bridges, railways, waterways, tunnels, and highways. The One Federal Decision Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) is an effort to streamline decision-making and reduce costly delays caused by inefficient environmental review processes. The administration believes that these improvements will benefit communities by delivering much-needed infrastructure projects.